IBADAN – As the party primaries draw nearer ahead of the 2023 gen­eral election, a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress, (APC) in Oyo State, precisely Oyo South Senatorial District, Olooye Adegboyega Adegoke has commenced grassroots mo­bilisation with the formation of contact and mobilisation team that will make his ambition a reality. The mandate of the team is to mobilise key stakeholders and members of the party in the nine local governments across the senatorial district to secure the party ticket at the forthcoming party primaries and eventually emerge victori­ous at the general election. The nine local governments of Oyo South Senatorial Dis­trict comprise Ibadan North, Ibadan North East, Ibadan North West, Ibadan South East, Ibadan South West, Ibarapa Central, Ibarapa East, Ibarapa North and Ido Local Govern­ment Areas. The team, which comprises three members each from each local government making 27 members will also appoint three members each from each ward of the nine local governments. Addressing the members of the team at the NIHORT Area, the venue of the inaugu­ration, Adegoke, a petroleum expert, real estate guru and a hotelier said the inauguration of the team is to kickstart the necessary consultation and mobilisation efforts aimed at securing the nod of all the stakeholders.